---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'January 7, 2026';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy">
  <main class="policy">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <section>
        <h2>What Data We Access</h2>
        <p>
          To provide optimization features, the app uses the YouTube Data API and YouTube Analytics API to
          fetch video content, performance metrics, and channel information for the logged-in YouTube
          account. Only data necessary to support these features is requested.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <p>
          Retrieved data is used to analyze performance and propose improvements. When you choose to apply
          changes, the app updates video metadata (such as titles, descriptions, tags, and thumbnails)
          through the YouTube APIs based on your interactions in the app.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Sharing with Third-Party AI Services</h2>
        <p>
          Some data returned from YouTube APIs may be processed by third-party AI tools, including OpenAI
          APIs, to generate suggestions and metadata updates. These services use the data only to support
          the requested improvements and do not receive ownership of your content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Performance Disclaimer</h2>
        <p>
          The app aims to improve channel performance by following industry best practices and YouTube
          recommendations. Outcomes may vary, and the app cannot be held responsible for decreased
          performance, including situations where user choices (for example, drastic manual changes to
          descriptions or hashtags) reduce results.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your Choices</h2>
        <p>
          You may disconnect your YouTube account at any time. You are responsible for reviewing suggested
          changes before they are applied and for complying with YouTube policies and applicable laws.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .policy {
    padding: var(--spacing-3xl) 0 var(--spacing-2xl);
    background: var(--gradient-bg);
  }

  h1 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  .meta {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-2xl);
  }

  section {
    background: var(--color-bg-elevated);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-lg);
    padding: var(--spacing-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
    box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  }

  section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }

  section p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .policy {
      padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0 var(--spacing-xl);
    }

    section {
      padding: var(--spacing-lg);
    }
  }
</style>

